<section id="how">
  <div class="section-label">Approach</div>
  <h2>How I <em>work</em></h2>
  <div class="how-grid">
    <div class="how-card fade-up">
      <span class="how-icon">I.</span>
      <h3>Process First, Then Scale</h3>
      <p>Before adding volume, I make sure the right processes are in place — clear SOPs, QA checkpoints, and defined roles. This keeps quality consistent as teams and client portfolios grow.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-card fade-up">
      <span class="how-icon">II.</span>
      <h3>Structured Communication Over Assumptions</h3>
      <p>I default to clarity. Whether managing a client relationship or coordinating across a delivery team, I set expectations early, communicate proactively, and make sure everyone involved has the context they need. Ambiguity tends to be where things go wrong — I work to remove it.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-card fade-up">
      <span class="how-icon">III.</span>
      <h3>Balancing Detail with the Bigger Picture</h3>
      <p>I move comfortably between strategy and execution. I can work at the level of a client growth roadmap or a specific delivery task — and I know when each one needs my attention. Getting the detail right matters, but not at the expense of losing sight of the overall direction.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-card fade-up">
      <span class="how-icon">IV.</span>
      <h3>Leading AI Adoption in the Team</h3>
      <p>I've led the integration of AI tools across team workflows to improve efficiency and output quality. The focus is practical: reducing manual effort, improving turnaround times, and maintaining quality at scale — not technology for its own sake.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-card fade-up">
      <span class="how-icon">V.</span>
      <h3>Developing the People Around Me</h3>
      <p>I've been involved in hiring, onboarding, and developing team members from day one. I invest in people's growth through structured training, regular feedback, and making sure they have what they need to do their jobs well.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="how-card fade-up">
      <span class="how-icon">VI.</span>
      <h3>Reporting That Drives Decisions</h3>
      <p>I build reporting frameworks that give clients and leadership clear visibility into performance. Good reporting isn't just about showing numbers — it's about helping people understand what's working and what to do next.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
